      "writtenOn": "2019-11-20T19:39:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "active implies CQ triggered this build, possibly indirectly (say CQ -\u003e compiler -\u003e tester)\n\na build with active\u003dfalse may still be waited by CQ, consider scenario:\n00:00 user does \"git cl try -b linux-rel\"\n00:01 bb -\u003e swarming -\u003e runs a recipe, where \u0027.active\u0027 is False.\n00:05 user does \"CQ+2\"\n~00:06 CQ starts running, notices existing linux-rel build and is now waiting on it.",
      "parentUuid": "f6546200_44cccfce",
      "revId": "4fad481cf700c1e26086d4d51fd69e51b0f97490",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
